# Brand Voice — Vibe Coders Academy

## Tone

- Clear, direct, practitioner-first — no hype or "10x" language.
- Confident but honest about what students will learn and what they won't.
- Short sentences. Active voice. Concrete outcomes over buzzwords.

## Audience

Developers and technical professionals who want to ship with AI agents (Cursor-first), not generic "learn to code" beginners.

## Avoid

- Guaranteed income, job placement, or "passive income" claims.
- Fake urgency ("last chance", "only 3 spots") unless Denis explicitly approves.
- Comparisons to competitors by name in public copy unless sourced in `research/competitors/`.

## Prefer

- "You will build X" over "You will master everything."
- Specific tool names (Cursor, MCP, automations) where relevant.
- One clear CTA per piece of content.

## Social

- LinkedIn: insight + lesson learned; 1–3 short paragraphs.
- X: one idea per post; thread only when necessary.
- Always align with `business/approved-messaging.md` for pricing and launch dates.
